AB  - This paper examines the overreaction hypothesis within the Spanish capital market. The hypothesis is clearly accepted even after correcting for size when estimating excess returns. Twelve months after portfolio formation, losers win 24.5% more than winners. There is also a correspondence between excess returns and changes in the earnings pattern of losers and winners firms.
