AB  - Current research on the relation between money and asset prices focuses on the reaction of asset prices to money supply announcements. In this paper we use the real interest observed in the U.K. index-linked bond market and the nominal interest rate observed in the nominal bond market to study the reaction of real interest rates and expected inflation to money surprises. We find that monetary surprises have a strong effect on inflationary expectations. We also find some evidence of a positive reaction of long-term real interest rates to the £M3 announcement.
