AB  - A model to price the call features embedded in Swiss riskless callable bonds is developed. The model accounts for the time-dependent variance of bond returns, the specific exercise conditions of this long term non-traded call option and the incompleteness of the Swiss bond market. Empirical results show that the call feature's price is particularly sensitive to the riskless rate and variance specifications. Illiquidity explains some cross sectional call pricing ‘biases’ found in this study but the underpricing of ordinary versus callable bonds cannot be excluded.
